    "pathophysiology": "Unclear trigger leads to polyclonal B-cell activation with IgG4 class switching. Lymphoplasmacytic infiltration with storiform fibrosis and obliterative phlebitis causes mass-forming or diffuse organ enlargement. In the biliary tree, this produces stricturing mimicking cholangiocarcinoma (IgG4-related cholangitis). In the pancreas, diffuse enlargement with a capsule-like rim (type 1 AIP). Elevated serum IgG4 and tissue IgG4+ plasma cells are hallmark but not pathognomonic.",
